The paper describes the development of a tactile-sensing finger for robot grasping, which falls under the field of robotics (cs.RO). The sensor uses optical techniques and image processing, which suggests a connection to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of tougher materials and a calibration process, which relates to the field of robotics and automation (cs.ROB). The use of image processing and machine learning for analyzing the tactile data could also fall under the category of multimedia (cs.MM) or machine learning (cs.LG).
